ratings.comment: Dr. Frazier is an AMAZING person. She's smart, funny, and very kind. The class is EXTREMELY easy, and it doesn't require hardly any work. Thought the class is easy, her curriculum and class structure has grown a little shaky over the past couple weeks. She's awesome, but I've seen less and less people paying attention. She tells a ton of stories.

Dr. Frazier's introductory class is my favorite so far at UW Madison, I really enjoyed the personal stories she shared as well as the weekly class discussions about a variety of different social issues. Furthermore, there was no textbook required or final exam, just essays, which were very manageable. I would highly recommend this class & professor
